Title: There are No Causality Problems for Fermi's Two Atom System
Authors: Detlev Buchholz and Jakob Yngvason
Comments: 6 pages, latex, DESY 94-027
Journal-ref: Phys.Rev.Lett. 73 (1994) 613-616
\\
  A repeatedly discussed gedanken experiment, proposed by Fermi to check
Einstein causality, is reconsidered. It is shown that, contrary to a recent
statement made by Hegerfeldt, there appears no causality paradoxon in a proper
theoretical description of the experiment.
